\key{Strength} allows you to carry more and to hit harder. Add the
bonus to your to-hit rolls and to your damage rolls when using
\emph{melee weapons}.

\key{Dexterity} allows you to aim better and to better avoid attacks.
Add the bonus to your to-hit roll when using \emph{ranged weapons}
(but not to your damage rolls) and subtract the bonus from your
\emph{armor class} (lower is better).

\key{Constitution} determines your health. Add the bonus to every
\emph{hit die} (but never reduce a hit die below 1).

\key{Intelligence} determines your education. If you have a positive
bonus, it indicates how many \emph{extra languages} you speak.

\key{Wisdom} determines how much in tune with the world you are. Add
the bonus to your \emph{saving throws against magic} (spells, wands
and the like).

\key{Charisma} determines how well others
\hyperref[key:Reaction Roll]{react} to you, how many
\hyperref[key:Retainers]{retainers and pets} will follow you (4 + your
bonus) and their \hyperref[key:Morale]{morale} score (7 + your
bonus).

\newthought{Choose your \index{Class}class}.

\hyperref[sec:fighter]{Fighter}: you can fight well; you will be able
to use magic swords; this is the simplest character to play
\marginnote[-2em]{\emph{What slaughter haunts your dreams? Whom do you
